AB  - In this note a more flexible restricted error covariance matrix is applied than Winters (1984) uses in order to estimate import demand functions. We show that the alternative specification performs better in the sense of yielding a considerably larger value of the log-likelihood function. Moreover, some slight errors in Winters' tables 2 and 3 are corrected.
